## Docker Compose

```bash
# Build and start all services
docker compose up -d --build

# View logs
docker compose logs -f app

# Run database migrations
docker compose exec app node dist/migrate.js

# Health check
curl http://localhost:3000/health
```

## Environment

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and fill in all values before deploying.

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with production values
```

## Pre-Deploy Checklist

- [ ] `.env` file exists with all required values
- [ ] Database is accessible from the app container
- [ ] `docker compose up -d --build` succeeds
- [ ] Health check endpoint returns 200
- [ ] Logs show no startup errors
